# Prologue profile: Safe minimal set for dump/restore
#
# This profile defines which .env/local/ variables are transferred in the PROLOGUE
# section of a dump (before protocol imports/adds/links execute).
#
# Purpose:
#   - Provides minimal environment needed for restore to work correctly
#   - Includes base interpreters (needed for restore execution model)
#   - Excludes function-specific interpreter overrides (prevent restore breakage)
#
# Included - Base interpreters (global execution control):
#   - VPN_SWITCH_TERMINAL_INTERPRETER (default: cat, user might override to sh)
#   - VPN_SWITCH_COMBINATOR_INTERPRETER (default: sh)
#   - VPN_SWITCH_BATCH_COMBINATOR_INTERPRETER (default: batch processor)
#
# Included - Configuration (paths, interfaces, firewall, DNS, display):
#   - VPN_SWITCH_PATH, VPN_SWITCH_WG, VPN_SWITCH_OPENVPN (binary paths)
#   - VPN_SWITCH_WG_INTERFACE, VPN_SWITCH_OVPN_INTERFACE (interface names)
#   - VPN_SWITCH_PFCTL, VPN_SWITCH_PF_CONF, firewall settings
#   - VPN_SWITCH_*_RESOLVCONF, VPN_SWITCH_VPN_DNS_TABLE (DNS)
#   - VPN_SWITCH_DISPLAY_ANSI, VPN_SWITCH_PHASES_* (behavior)
#
# Excluded - Function-specific interpreter overrides:
#   - VPN_SWITCH_INTERPRETER_import (if cat, imports won't copy files!)
#   - VPN_SWITCH_INTERPRETER_add (if cat, directories won't be created!)
#   - VPN_SWITCH_INTERPRETER_link (if cat, symlinks won't be created!)
#   - VPN_SWITCH_INTERPRETER_* (all other function-specific overrides)
#
# These function-specific interpreters are applied in the EPILOGUE (after restore
# completes) to restore the user's full environment configuration.
#
# Phase 3.1.4: Dump/restore prologue/epilogue separation
